\section*{QUANTITATIVE ANALYSIS OF KETONES IN THE MANAGEMENT OF DIABETES MELLITUS INTRODUCTION}
- Energy required for metabolic activities is delivered from glucose
- Insulin and glucagon are important hormones that control blood glucose.
- Made and secreted by the pancrease but have opposite roles
- Insulin enhances entry of glucose into the cells
- Insulin insufficiency, insensitivity and deficiency results causes diabetes mellitus(DM)
- Types of DM of great medical importance -
- IDDM(Type 1 DM),NIDDM(Type 2DM) and gestational DM
- Insulin inactivity causes the body to source energy from fats resulting with formation of ketones
- Three types of ketones---acetone, acetoactate and $\boldsymbol{\beta}$-hydroxybutyrate
- Under normal metabolic conditions ketones do not accumulate in blood therefore undetectable
- During starvation, after exercise or at night
- In DM ketones level rises due to:-
- (i)rise in blood glucose levels due to insulin inactivity----No entry of glucose into ICF
- (ii)body cells burning fat for energy production
- (iii) continuous accumulation of ketones as fat is used as source of energy
- Diabetic ketoacidosis (DKA) is a complication which results from accumulation of ketones in the circulation of a diabetic patient
- $\beta$-hydroxybutyrate is the ketone related to the development of DKA
- DKA is more common in IDDM than in NIDDM and DKA is a potentially lethal in either case of DM.

